abstract: Noting that there are already women running "midlevel banks," Senator Kirsten E. Gillibrand, Democrat of New York, told an audience on Wednesday that a woman would probably rise to the top of one of the nation's five biggest banks before a woman became president, Bloomberg News reports.

headline.main: A Woman Wall Street C.E.O. Before a Woman President?
